history.content:
Maybe an advisor can respond to help you decide which class to enroll in.

I can tell you that CS170 does have discussion sections. You can see when they are held on classes.berkeley.edu.

New for Fall 2017, you can only enroll in the lecture and section 999 via campus solutions. This is by design to avoid the issue of being bumped to the end of the lecture wait list any time you want to change sections. Instead, you enroll in section 999 and wait until the beginning of class to determine which actual section you will attend.

Professors will either put information on the course home page about this and/or discuss this during the first lecture.

I am a rising sophomore EECS major with a July 31 Phase 2. Should I phase 2 CS61C or CS170. CS170 has 343 seats open with 175 seats still reserved for EECS. It also does not have scheduled discussion sections. CS61C has 401 open seats, with 266 reserved for EECS. They do seem to have scheduled discussion sections.
history.subject: Phase 2: CS170 or CS61C
